class Solution {
    public int compress(char[] chars) {
        int count = 1;
        int result = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < chars.length; i++) {
            if (chars[i] == chars[i + count]) {
                count++;
            } else {
                chars[result++] = chars[i];
                chars[result++] = count;
                count = 1;
            }
        }
        return result;
    }
}
```

efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW

Explanation:

The algorithm iterates through the input array once using a for loop. It checks if the current character is the same as the previous one. If they are the same, it increments the count variable. Otherwise, it appends the character and its count to the result array and resets the count to 1. This ensures that consecutive characters of the same type are grouped together and represented by their count. The algorithm returns the length of the result array after processing the entire array.

The time complexity is O(n) because the algorithm iterates through the array once. The space complexity is O(1) because the algorithm only uses a small constant amount of space for the result array and count variable. The energy implications are low because the algorithm does not consume significant energy.

